claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for holding and obtaining an item, comprising: 
a housing; 
a plurality of drawer trays contained in said housing wherein each of said plurality of trays contains one or more drawers, each of said one or more drawers comprising: 
a plurality of compartments that are capable of storing the item; 
a striker plate; 
a solenoid-controlled latch wherein said latch engages said striker plate to lock said drawer in place when said latch is not energized; 
a raster strip; and 
three photodetectors located in proximity to each other and located in proximity to said raster strip wherein said three photodetectors illuminate light towards said raster strip; and 

a controller communicatively coupled to each said latch for said one or more drawers wherein said controller is adapted to energize said latch to disengage each said latch from said striker plate to unlock said one or more drawers; 
said controller adapted to receive a transaction request for the item in said housing and wherein said controller de-energizes said latch to lock said one of said one or more drawers when all of said three photodetectors are occluded.

17. An apparatus for receiving control information from a remote computer and holding and storing an item, comprising: 
a housing; 
a plurality of drawer trays contained in said housing wherein each of said plurality of trays contains one or more drawers, each of said one or more drawers comprising: 
a plurality of compartments that are capable of storing the item; 
a striker plate; and 
a latch wherein said latch engages said striker plate to lock said drawer in place; 

a modem adapted to receive control information relating to said one or more drawers from the remote computer; and 
a controller adapted to receive said control information from said modem wherein said controller is communicatively coupled to each said latch for said one or more drawers, and wherein said controller is adapted to disengage said latch from said striker plate to unlock said one or more drawers based on the control information.

27. An apparatus for transmitting a warning message to a remote computer for restocking of items, comprising: 
a housing; 
a plurality of drawer trays contained in said housing wherein each of said plurality of trays contains one or more drawers, each of said one or more drawers comprising: 
a plurality of compartments that are capable of storing the item; 
a striker plate; and 
a latch wherein said latch engages said striker plate to lock said drawer in place; 

a modem; and 
a controller communicatively coupled to said modem and adapted to determine the inventory information relating to the items in said one or more drawers and further adapted to transmit a warning message using said modem when said one or more drawers need replenishing.

51. A method for allowing a user to request an item to access the item, comprising: 
swiping a card having a magnetic stripe through a magnetic stripe card reader to read card information off of said card; 
selecting the item to access; 
determining if access to the item is authorized based on said card information, and if authorized, then comprising the steps of: 
determining which one of a plurality of drawers contains the item requested; 
unlocking said one of said plurality of drawers that contains the item requested; 
illuminating a light source on said one of said plurality of drawers based that contains the item requested; and 
opening said one of said plurality of drawers to obtain the item.
